cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the deployment of base stations and multi-antenna techniques for future mobile networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The concept of technical rate of substitution (TRS) from microeconomics is introduced and studied in the paper, which is related to information theory.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper discusses spectrum sharing techniques and utilization of higher frequency bands for more bandwidth, which is related to communications and networking.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the provisioning of extremely fast mobile broadband, which is related to multimedia applications.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses system design for future mobile networks, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
